headline: SuperX Appoints Former Intel GM Ken Lau as Chief Strategy Officer and Executive Director to Strengthen Global Supply Chain
summary: SuperX AI Technology Limited (NASDAQ: SUPX) ("the Company" or "SuperX") today announced the appointment of Mr. Ken Lau as the Company's Chief Strategy Officer (CSO) and Executive Director of the Board, concurrently serving as Chief Executive Officer (CEO) of its Singapore subsidiary, SuperX Industries Pte. Ltd. ("SuperX Industries"). The appointment will take effect on December 1, 2025.

headline: Looking at the Changing Narrative for Intel Amid Analyst Debates and Industry Shifts
summary: Intel’s stock narrative is evolving in response to a recent price target update. The fair value remains steady at $37.27 per share, while the discount rate has increased from 11.64% to 11.78%. This adjustment reflects both optimism around Intel's execution and clarity in its AI strategy, as well as caution about execution risks and industry dynamics. Stay tuned for insights on how to track Intel’s story as market perspectives continue to evolve. Stay updated as the Fair Value for Intel shifts...
